sec.p:
Our nomogram predicted probabilities of COVID-19 with an area under the receiver operating characteristic curve of 0.913 (95% confidence interval [CI], 0.883–0.937), greater than that of the lymphocyte:monocyte ratio (0.849; 95% CI, 0.812–0.880; 
   P = .0007), lymphocyte percentage (0.808; 95% CI, 0.768–0.843; 
   P < .0001), monocyte count (0.780; 95% CI, 0.739–0.817; 
   P < .0001), or age (0.656; 95% CI, 0.610–0.699; 
   P < .0001). The predicted probability conformed to the real observation outcomes of COVID-19, according to the calibration curves.
